lain why he switched from windows to mac on gearlog radio download the mp the here and now two weeks ago while browsing through a stack of dvds stored in my livingroom closet i stumbled across two different videos shot at my wedding one by my fatherinlaw and the other by a friend id always intended to edit these two videos together and dub in music whenever the audio went south but manipulating audio and video can be a pain on windows ive used adobe premiere before and in my experience sometimes it works and sometimes it crashes i had no desire to spend the summer weekends ripping out my hair how about using imovie a colleague asked if only i had a mac i responded but wait i was in the market to buy a new computer related still have questions about switching to a macintel system still have questions about switching to a macintel system apple macbook inch apple macbook inch apple imac intel core duo apple imac intel core duo i live in a windows world at home and the office and historically macs dont play nicely in a windows world but with the advent of the core duo t  ghz processor in the macbook it all changed macs could now run on windows if absolutely necessary via apples boot camp  note that i had no intention of installing windows on a macand im not just saying this to save face with my bossbut it was nice to know the option existed and with that the last of my reservations fell away i drove to the apple store and bought an apple macbook inch with a ghz processor gb hard drive and gb of memory for  because my wife is a student they gave us a free gb ipod nano a free hp photosmart c allinone printer and  off microsoft office  necessary to stay compatible with work killer deal i smiled all the way home until my wife reminded me that it was our third anniversary and i had purchased myself an expensive gift even with the threat of spending my weekend nights sleeping on the couch i ripped open the box and booted os x tiger for the first time at home welcome back ol